INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (549,'node',' athens technical college 2011 present participating institution http wwwathenstechedu  athens technical college s goal is to use the findings of indepth data analyses to develop and implement researchbased policies and practices that improve student performance in a number of key areas the longterm goals of athens tech include support for more students enrolling in higher education create more college graduates who earn higher wages as part of a highlyskilled state and national workforce athens tech has recently completed a twoyear strategic planning process that enabled the college to identify what it must undertake to improve its most salient goal of improving student performance athens tech must reduce student attrition rates emphasize improvement in learning support and gatekeeper courses reduce performance gaps among diverse groups of students with the help of faculty and professional development the college plans to use the guidance of achieving the dream to provide ways to accomplish these strategic initiatives increase opportunities for student success decrease the dropout rate and diminish poverty by preparing students for the diverse workforce and increasing their options athens technical college is the first college in georgia to participate as an achieving the dream institution the institution is aiming its efforts at improving student success closing achieving gaps and increasing students persistence and graduation rates athens tech is highly concerned with the high poverty rate in the athensclarke county area which is more than twice that of the state of georgia s average particularly among young adults which the college mostly serves a little over half 51 of the student population is under the age of 25 the college offers more than 100 technical certificate diploma and associate degree programs of study that provide students with the educational foundation they need to work in a variety of fields in the 10 county areas surrounding athens athens tech enrollment has increased almost 30 over the past five years to a total of 5170 students enrolled in the fall of 2009 during the same period completion rates among firsttime college students increased from 28 to 31 however the college s data show that 27 of the students enrolled in academic programs of study during the 20092010 academic year had to take one or more learning support courses furthermore data show that 33 of the students who took learning support courses in math either failed or withdrew from the courses almost 60 of undergraduates attend the college parttime and 23 of athens tech total enrollment is african american we had spent more than two years discussing our future and what we wanted our college to look like in 2015 and our faculty and staff wanted to know what we could do better that would help students realize their educational goals flora w tydings president athens technical college  ',0);
INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (550,'node',' austin community college 2009 present participating institution http wwwaustinccedu  austin community college has given a cohesive and comprehensive face to student success since 2009 acc has pursued multiple student success strategies under the comprehensive umbrella of its student success initiative ssi the college has established a student success initiative steering committee ssisc comprised of students faculty and college leadership which sets and pursues multiple strategies all aimed at closing achievement gaps and improving overall student success the ssi has seven goals those goals are to reduce attrition increase the numbers of students who complete developmental and adult education course progression to credit courses increase the numbers of students who complete gateway courses increase student persistence term to term year to year enhance student learning by increasing the numbers of students who complete attempted courses with a c or better increase the degree certificate graduates transfer rates and increase success equity across all racial ethnic gender income groups acc has also created and continues to scale the following four interventions to close achievement gaps at the college mandatory orientation mathematical thinking matd 385 developmental math advisors and a faculty coach program austin community college acc enrolls more than 44000 credit students with an additional 15000 students enrolled in noncredit courses acc is an open door to higher education and training serving an eightcounty service area in central texas acc is the leading source of transfer students to the university of texasaustin and texas state university at san marcos and is the number one choice for high school graduates and adults who enter college acc provides educational programs and support services that produce the backbone of the local workforce in 2009 acc launched a student success initiative to assure the student succ