INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (1957,'node',' baby boomer warren james of cleveland enrolls at cuyahoga community college after losing job by robert schoenberger cleveland ohio the instructor in the shop looks younger than warren james daughter james spent more than half his life working with specialty metals running multimillion dollar equipment now at 56 the cleveland man is without a job and back in school learning advanced manufacturing alongside teenagers i would have topped out at about 27 an hour and change i had 30 days of vacation they had a good 401k program said james who worked at csm industries from 1977 to 2009 it was a good job i was making decent money he couldn t get his footing after losing his job he invested his severance pay into a new carpentry business and took a loss on his first major job despite his 30plus years in manufacturing all he could find was temp work a few months at one job a few days at another on top of that his wife annette had to take a pay cut bills were piling up and they lost their home to foreclosure retirement savings and money james had hoped to put towards his son and daughter s education went away as well he knew something had to change my mom had me at 19 my brother at 16 she started back to school from 10th grade with two kids there was no father in the home james said she went to tric and got her nursing degree she never gave up so i never thought i could he realized that the skills he learned on the job weren t going to help him find his next one he s now taking classes at cuyahoga community college s unified technology center james is focusing his efforts in school on learning how to run cnc machines computerprogrammed tools used in almost every manufacturing plant in the country by april he hopes to win certifications for operating and programming such tools he s already gotten a few interviews and assurances from companies that they need skilled cnc people james is confident that he won t be unemployed much