INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (2689,'node',' kickoff 2012 june 1013 in portland or what is kickoff institute  kickoff institute is where your first year as an achieving the dream institution officially begins participants will work with their coaches to gain an understanding of the achieving the dream mission values and approaches to the studentcentered model of institutional improvement together critical tasks will be identified and a plan and action steps will be developed by the end of kickoff institute participants will have stronger knowledge and skills for integrating student equity success and completion agenda and to strengthen the commitment to making evidencebased decisions  what is included with my participation in achieving the dream  your participation in achieving the dream entitles you to five registrations to the kickoff institute five members of your core team should attend president director of institutional research academic dean dean of student services a key faculty leader the following meals are included opening dinner sunday june 10 at 6 pm breakfast a full day of events and lunch monday june 11 breakfast a full day of events and lunch tuesday june 12 breakfast a half day of events and a box lunch wednesday june 13 what is not included   travel and ground transportation colleges are responsible for arranging and funding their travel to and from the kickoff institute as well as their lodging please see how will i get to kickoff institute below for information on ground transportation hotel colleges are responsible for arranging and funding lodging for the kickoff institute please how do i reserve a hotel room for kickoff institute below for hotel registration information dinner on monday june 11 2012 and tuesday june 12 2012 dinner for monday and tuesday will be on your own however many colleges use the monday and tuesday dinner hours as additional time to meet with their team leadership coach and or data coach how do i register for kickoff institute    register here  please complete the registration form via adobe forms once the registration form is complete an automatic confirmation will be sent to the email address provided if you have any questions in the meantime regarding registration please contact kennard shirley at kshirley achievingthedreamorg or 240 4503816  can i send more than 5 representatives from my college   often colleges wish to send more than five attendees in order to ensure the best possible experience for attendees we cannot guarantee registrations for additional people beyond the core team members however if you wish to send additional attendees please have these individuals select the i would like to be on the wait list option on the registration form no later than friday may 4 2012 once we have heard from all the new colleges we will confirm which additional attendees are approved to attend kickoff please note while registration fees for the first five attendees from each college are included in your annual participation fee there is a registration fee of approximately 550 person for approved additional attendees travel costs for all attendees are the responsibility of the colleges where is kickoff institute 2012   all kickoff institute meetings will take place in portland or at portland marriott downtown waterfront 1401 sw naito parkway portland or 97201  how do i reserve a hotel room for kickoff institute   a block of rooms for has been reserved for kickoff institute participants at the conference rate of 135 plus tax per night college representatives are responsible for making their hotel reservations by friday may 18 2012 reservations can be made online on our dedicated hotel booking website or by calling reservations toll free 18779016632 or reservations local phone 15064742009 referencing achieving the dream kickoff 2012 please note hotel reservations made by any other method than described above are not guaranteed the conference room rate how will i get to kickoff institute   airport  portland international airport pdx  is located 9 miles from the portland marriott downtown waterfront driving directions from pdx take airport way east to i205 south then take i84 west to the city center city center oregon city exit continue to follow signs to city center cross morrison bridge and take naito parkway exit and turn right hotel is 12 mile on right ground transportation light rail there is a light rail system that goes from the airport to downtown portland for 240 one way the light rail station is walking distance from the marriott please visit trimet light rail for more information on public transportation in downtown portland taxi the estimated taxi fare from pdx is 35 one way airport shuttle the estimated cost for a scheduled airport shuttle is 14 one way please note the portland marriott downtown waterfront does not provide shuttle service to or from pdx parking kickoff participants will receive a 25 discount on parking at the portland marriott downtown waterfront how do i prepare for kickoff institute   if you haven t already done so please complete the achieving the dream college contact information spreadsheet and submit it to info achievingthedreamorg no later than april 17 2012 as we receive completed contact sheets we add those individuals to our listservs so that they can start receiving general achieving the dream communications achieving the dream listservs include one for presidents and chancellors one for core team leaders and one for public information officers atd readiness assessment a completed copy of your college s readiness assessment  previously sent to you is due to info achievingthedreamorg by april 20 2012 your completed assessment will be shared with your leadership coach and data coach and used during planning sessions at the institute please bring copies for each member of your team colleges are encouraged to involve as many college representatives as possible in this selfassessment especially faculty what to bring  each participant should bring a laptop with wifi capability and at least one usb port we will provide you with a thumb drive containing templates and other materials to use during workshop planning sessions in addition please bring a copy of your academic calendar to help during the planning process  how can i access resources after the institute is over  for your convenience we have posted all resources on our site for you to access on the kickoff institute resources page   kickoff 2012  ',0);
