INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (3337,'node',' angel niederkohr sc4 makes students welcome a new group of students will join returning students at st clair county community college this fall some will be coming to college right out of high school others will be returning to school after a gap to make the transition easier all these students will experience a revised orientation process the new inperson orientation helps students become better acquainted with the college its support services and extracurricular activities the idea is to provide students with a warm welcome while connecting them with the tools they need to succeed during orientation students meet other incoming freshmen they learn what is expected of them at sc4 they learn how to take advantage of sc4 s many support services from tutoring to financial aid and employment services they also get tips for avoiding common problems experienced by firsttime college students the session is interactive to get students engaged and they don t just hear from presenters but also from sc4 professors in a video filled with tips for their success the orientation goes beyond the classroom students get familiar with sc4 s campus on a tour they meet staff in campus offices and see where they will be attending class students also log into their online accounts and walk through how to register for classes check their financial aid status submit payments and make advising appointments they learn how to use sc4 s schedule planning tool an online system that helps students easily plan their schedules the new orientation is helping to better connect students to our campus and remove barriers to student success when new students arrive at sc4 they no longer need to spend time searching for their classes or attempting to log in to their student accounts the orientation first debuted in fall 2011 and is now mandatory for new students students previously only completed their orientation online the new orientation sc4 99 is inperson to help students better retain information as they interact with sc4 s campus and staff the threehour session is led by student services staff and student ambassadors it gives students a comprehensive introduction to sc4 and student life feedback has been positive students have remarked that after the sessions they feel more prepared to take on the challenges of college the revised orientation process stemmed from sc4 s participation in achieving the dream community colleges count a national nonprofit organization that helps colleges identify strategies to improve student success close achievement gaps and increase retention persistence and completion rates it is another way we are seeking to empower students and prepare them to reach their goals angel niederkohr is student activities orientation and international programs coordinator at st clair county community college http wwwthetimesheraldcom article 20120624 opinion02306240017 angelniederk  the times herald  ',0);
