INSERT INTO `search_dataset` VALUES (3932,'node',' arthur scott leadership coach dr arthur l scott was installed as president of northampton community college in july of 2003 and retired from the presidency in july of 2012 upon retirement dr scott was named president emeritus and the college s athletic center was named the arthur l scott spartan center in his honor dr scott holds the edd and med both from lehigh university and a bachelor s degree from gettysburg college while studying at lehigh he was named a university scholar and received the matthew w gaffney award for academic excellence joining the northampton staff in 1976 dr scott served the college in many ways first as director of records then as director of admissions vice president of student affairs chief labor negotiator overseer of college services as provost and finally as president in addition to his duties at northampton he also served as an adjunct professor in the college of education at lehigh university early in his career he was a high school teacher throughout his tenure as president credit enrollment at northampton grew by 49 and by 2012 over 35000 students were enrolled in either credit or noncredit programs in addition under dr scott s leadership an emphasis was placed not only on access but on student success as well named an achieving the dream college atd in 2006 and an atd leader college in 2010 the first in pennsylvania northampton s graduation numbers have increased dramatically as the entire college community has become committed to student completion active in the community dr scott currently serves on the boards of the st luke s hospital and health network and the lehigh valley industrial park inc in past years dr scott was instrumental in the creation of one united way for the lehigh valley during his tenure as chair of the board of united way of northampton and warren counties he helped to found leadership lehigh valley and is a past chair of its board dr scott was also president of the board of directors of community services for children and past chairman of pa campus compact in 2012 dr scott received the priscilla payne hurd award from the lehigh valley chamber of commerce for his contributions to improving the quality of life in the lehigh valley in 2008 he was the recipient of the ywca of bethlehem velvet hammer award for outstanding commitment to racial justice and served as the light the night corporate walk chairman for the leukemia lymphomas society in 2004 he was honored with the inez and edward donley award for advocacy for children presented by community services for children  ',0);
